Team














Client Relationships team.



 





				Jodan Ledford			



		Head of Client Solutions and Multi-Asset	









close



Jodan Ledford
Head of Client Solutions and Multi-Asset




Jodan joined LGIMA in 2013 as Head of US Solutions. In 2017, Jodan expanded his role to the Head of Client Solutions and Multi-Asset, which includes oversight over each of the Distribution, Client Relationships, Solutions strategy, Product and Multi-Asset portfolio management areas. 
Prior to joining LGIMA, Jodan was executive director and business head of asset liability investment solutions at UBS Global Asset Management. Prior to UBS, Jodan worked at J.P. Morgan in the Investment Bank, where he worked in an advisory capacity. Jodan began his career as an actuarial analyst at Watson Wyatt Worldwide, where he worked as consultant to large (>$50 billion) US defined benefit pension plans and post-retirement welfare plans.
Jodan holds a BA in Mathematics from Emory University and an MS in Applied Statistics from the University of Miami, School of Business.
 








				Bradley S. Wynn			



		Head of Client Relationship Management	









close



Bradley S. Wynn
Head of Client Relationship Management




Brad joined LGIMA in 2013. As a Senior Client Relationship Manager, and was promoted to Head of Client Relationship Management in 2015. Brad focuses on active fixed income and LDI clients, fitting our expertise to solving client problems.
Prior to joining LGIMA, Brad was an Executive Director at Morgan Stanley, and most recently served as head of the Chicago credit desk. Previously, Brad held positions at Goldman Sachs, Bear Stearns and TD Securities. Brad brings with him  more than two decades of experience working with institutional fixed income clients, including pension plans, insurance companies and leveraged clients, primarily in corporate credit, mortgage-backed securities and structured products.
Brad holds a BS in Economics from The Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania and a MBA from Northwestern University’s Kellogg Graduate School of Management.
 








				Jeff Eberhardt			



		Senior Client Relationship Manager	









close



Jeff Eberhardt
Senior Client Relationship Manager




Jeff joined LGIMA in 2014 as a Senior Client Relationship Manager. Jeff’s main responsibility is to be the primary contact for clients implementing customized and sophisticated LDI solutions.
Prior to joining LGIMA, Jeff held positions with Ansley Capital Group, Deutsche Bank, Wachovia Securities, Bank of America and Nomura Securities.  Jeff has extensive middle office and front office experience in origination, structuring and execution in asset backed, CDO, equity linked, hybrid and derivative instruments.
Jeff earned his BSc from The London School of Economics and Political Science and his MBA from The University of Chicago Booth School of Business.
 








				Christy Whittington			



		Senior Client Relationship Manager	









close



Christy Whittington
Senior Client Relationship Manager




Christy joined LGIMA in 2014 as a Senior Client Relationship Manager. Christy serves as the primary contact for clients investing in active fixed income and LDI strategies, fitting our expertise to solving client problems.
Prior to joining LGIMA, Christy was Manager of Retirement Investments at FedEx Corporation where she had the primary responsibility of monitoring the LDI program and opportunistic fixed income managers.  Prior to FedEx, Christy was a Senior Consultant at Consulting Services Group, LLC, where she advised institutional and high net worth clients on their investment programs.
Christy holds a BBA in Banking & Finance and Managerial Finance from the University of Mississippi and an Executive MBA from the University of Memphis.  She has also earned the CIMA certification. 
 








				Peter E. Kelly			



		Senior Client Relationship Manager	









close



Peter E. Kelly
Senior Client Relationship Manager




Peter joined LGIMA in 2016 as a Senior Client Relationship Manager where he serves as the primary contact for active fixed income, LDI and index clients, fitting our expertise to solving client problems.
Prior to joining LGIMA, Peter was a Vice President at Goldman Sachs focused on client coverage and relationship management of large institutional fixed income clients.  Previously, Peter held positions at Paine Webber, Kidder Peabody and Drexel Burnham Lambert.  With a particular focus on mortgage-backed securities and structured products Peter brings more than three decades of experience covering asset managers, pension funds, insurance companies and commercial banks.
Peter holds a BA in both Philosophy and Economics from Boston College and a MBA from the University of Michigan Ross School of Business.
 








				Rachel Madsen			



		Client Relationship Manager	









close



Rachel Madsen
Client Relationship Manager




Rachel joined LGIMA in 2015 as a Senior Client Relationship Associate. In 2017, Rachel was promoted to Client Relationship Manager, and will continue to support senior members of the team, serving as an advocate and resource for our institutional client base.Prior to joining LGIMA, Rachel was Vice President, Marketing Director with Security Capital Research & Management, Inc., a boutique real-estate securities firm wholly-owned by J.P. Morgan, and held various other positions at J.P. Morgan, William Blair & Company, AIM Investments Inc., and UBS. Rachel has diverse experience in institutional investor relations and new business development as well as fundamental equity research and capital markets analysis. Rachel is a CFA charterholder and graduated with honors from Westmont College with a BA in Economics and Business.
 








				Andrew Westman			



		Onboarding Specialist	









close



Andrew Westman
Onboarding Specialist




Andrew joined LGIMA in 2016. He is responsible for the coordination and implementation of new client mandates and existing client portfolio amendments in partnership with impacted stakeholder teams. Additionally, Andrew helps ensure that all legal, operational, compliance and transitional requirements are comprehensively identified, tasked and completed.Prior to LGIMA, Andrew spent almost 13 years at Northern Trust in a variety of rolls in operations, client servicing and most recently as an investment product manager working primarily on large restructures and rebalances across a broad client base in the custody and asset management divisions.Andrew graduated with a BA in Politics from the University of Dallas and earned an MBA in Financial Services from the University of Dallas Graduate School of Management.      
 








				Chris Huff			



		Head of Client Services	









close



Chris Huff
Head of Client Services




Chris joined LGIMA in 2014 as Manager of the Investment Analytics and Reporting Team. In 2017, he was promoted to Head of Client Services with continued responsibility for analytics and client reporting. Prior to joining LGIMA, Chris spent over 10 years with FactSet Research Systems in various roles, where he led teams in implementing and supporting risk analytics solutions for asset managers, insurance companies and pension funds.Chris earned his BS in Software Engineering from Fairfield University and his MBA from The University of Chicago Booth School of Business.
 









