Legal & General Investment Management America Inc. Key Developments

Legal & General Investment Management America Announces Appointment of Kathleen Gallagher to Board of Directors
May 9 17
Legal & General Investment Management America Inc. announced that Kathleen Gallagher has been appointed to the Board of Directors, effective May 1. Ms. Gallagher is the former Chief Investment Officer - Benefit Plans for Ford Motor Company. Ms. Gallagher recently retired after 31 years at Ford.


Legal & General Investment Management America Appoints Jodan Ledford to Head of Client Solutions and Multi-Asset
Feb 21 17
Legal & General Investment Management America Inc. announced that Jodan Ledford will expand his role from Head of US Solutions to Head of Client Solutions and Multi-Asset. With this move, LGIMA is focusing on evolving client engagement to bring them closer to the investment experience and ensure that the best of LGIMA is delivered to clients. Jodan will lead the Distribution and Client Relationship teams while continuing in his current role overseeing the Solutions, Multi-Asset Portfolio Management and Product groups. Unifying the teams under one division ensures that LGIMA delivers the best-in-class client experience aligned to their needs and evolving preferences.


Legal & General Investment Management America Announces Executive Changes
Nov 10 16
Legal & General Investment Management (LGIM) has announced the appointment of Aaron Meder as CEO of Legal & General Investment Management America (LGIMA)1 and Anton Eser as Chief Investment Officer. Both roles will report into Mark Zinkula, CEO of LGIM2. Aaron will transition into the role over the next few months and will be based in Chicago. Anton, currently Co-Head of LGIM's Global Fixed Income business, will succeed Aaron when he takes up his new role in Chicago. Colin Reedie, currently Head of Euro Credit, will replace Anton as Co-Head of Global Fixed Income, alongside John Bender, also CIO of US Fixed Income.


